race.comment: CANYA HANDLE IT (2) wound up strongly to score two back then did the same last time but could manage only a placing, finishing on late when third (23.54) in a Grade 5 at this track. Has a strong winning record here. Was a winner at his only start from this draw. Must come into calculations. OUTPLAYED (1) got around 450m in a strong 25.39 when winning a Grade 5 at Grafton last start. Top win latest and can measure up again. BURGLAR TOM (6) jumped from a middle draw last time and could manage only fourth and beaten 2.5 lengths (30.26) at Gosford. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. TINY SNIFFY (8) is one of the chances after collecting a minor prize last time.
